Info2: <<
Package: svnadmin-db%type_pkg[bdb]
Version: 1.5.5
Revision: 1
Description: Svnadmin tool linked to BDB %type_raw[bdb]
Type: bdb (4.1 4.2 4.3 4.4)
License: BSD
Maintainer: Daniel Johnson <daniel@daniel-johnson.org>

# Dependencies:
Depends: (%type_pkg[bdb] >= 44) db%type_pkg[bdb]-aes-shlibs | (%type_pkg[bdb] <= 43) db%type_pkg[bdb]-ssl-shlibs | db%type_pkg[bdb]-shlibs, libiconv, libgettext3-shlibs, expat1-shlibs, sqlite3-shlibs
BuildDepends: fink (>= 0.16.0-1), (%type_pkg[bdb] >= 44) db%type_pkg[bdb]-aes | (%type_pkg[bdb] <= 43) db%type_pkg[bdb]-ssl | db%type_pkg[bdb], system-openssl-dev, texinfo (>= 4.2-22), libiconv-dev (>= 1.9.1-11), gettext-bin, gettext-tools, libgettext3-dev, io-string-pm, expat1, sqlite3-dev

# Unpack Phase:
Source: http://subversion.tigris.org/downloads/subversion-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: 6f3701a0f2acf3fe53093491ba3d77ee
Source2: http://subversion.tigris.org/downloads/subversion-deps-%v.tar.bz2
Source2-MD5: 2a6e6d605f1767ea8e7f9db5b2b60f17

# Compile Phase:
NoSetLDFLAGS: true
NoSetLIBS: true
SetLDFLAGS: -L%p/lib/system-openssl/lib -L%p/lib

ConfigureParams: --libexecdir='${prefix}/lib/svn15' --without-neon --without-serf --disable-shared --enable-all-static --without-apxs --without-apache --disable-mod-activation --without-jdk --disable-javahl --with-jikes=no --without-swig --with-berkeley-db=%p/include/db4:%p/lib
GCC: 4.0
CompileScript: <<
#! /bin/sh -ev
 ### Configure static
 export F77=no; ./configure %c

 ### make apr static
 make external-all
 
 ### make svnadmin static 
 make svnadmin
<<

# Install Phase:
DocFiles: BUGS CHANGES COMMITTERS COPYING HACKING INSTALL README
InstallScript: <<
 /usr/bin/install -d %i/bin
  cd subversion/svnadmin ; /bin/sh %b/libtool --mode=install /usr/bin/install -c svnadmin %i/bin/svnadmin-db%type_pkg[bdb]
<<

# Additional Info
DescDetail: <<
Statically linked version of the svnadmin tool used to dump subversion
repositories created with an older version of the Berkeley DB.
<<
DescUsage: <<
To dump a svn repository built under an older Berkeley DB version
do the following:
- fink install svnadmin-db%type_pkg[bdb]
- svnadmin-db%type_pkg[bdb] dump myrepos
- fink install svn
- svnadmin load newrepos

Please read

http://subversion.tigris.org/faq.html#dumpload

for more details.
<<
Homepage: http://subversion.tigris.org/
<<
